oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: People at Cumberland Gap
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: A view from above at the Pinnacle, Cumberland Gap. A wooden structure appears in foreground, as well as a woman, looking through a camera, and a man, in all white clothing, standing on rock formation. A sign indicates the direction of different states.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Tennessee Department of Conservation Photograph Collection, 1937-1976
